Today is National Coming Out Day, a day to celebrate the bravery of LGBTQ+ individuals who live authentically and create supportive communities. The article emphasizes the commitment of the current administration to ensure LGBTQ+ people can live openly and freely. It highlights the progress made in terms of protections and equal opportunities, such as preventing discrimination and allowing transgender individuals to serve in the military. However, the article acknowledges that there is still work to be done, as anti-LGBTQ+ bills persist and bullying and harassment continue, particularly affecting young transgender individuals and LGBTQ+ people of color. The administration pledges to stand against hate and protect the rights, safety, and mental health of LGBTQ+ individuals. The article concludes by affirming love and support for LGBTQ+ individuals and a commitment to fighting for their equality, dignity, and respect.